        </div>
      </div>

      <AnalystNotes
        title="Why This Comparison Is Different"
        icon="âš”ï¸"
        id="comparison-context"
        variant="light"
      >
        <h4>Elite vs Elite</h4>
        <p>Most broker comparisons have a clear winner. This isn't one of them. Pepperstone and IC Markets are both top-tier ECN brokers used by professional traders, hedge fund managers, and algorithmic trading firms. We're splitting hairs here.</p>

        <h5>What They Have in Common</h5>
        <p>Both offer raw spreads from 0.0 pips, identical commission rates ($3.50/lot), the same platforms (MT4, MT5, cTrader, TradingView), free VPS hosting, and excellent execution. Both are ASIC-regulated with segregated client funds. If you closed your eyes and picked one, you'd be fine.</p>

        <h5>Where Pepperstone Edges Ahead</h5>
        <p>Accessibility (no minimum deposit), regulatory breadth (BaFin, FCA), and slightly faster execution. Better for: new traders, European traders, and those prioritizing regulatory protection.</p>

        <h5>Where IC Markets Edges Ahead</h5>
        <p>Liquidity depth ($1T+ monthly volume), instrument range, and slightly tighter spreads on average. Better for: high-volume traders, EA developers, and those trading beyond forex.</p>

        <h5>The Real Decision Factor</h5>
        <p>Honestly? Pick based on where you're located (regulation matters), minimum deposit requirements, or which interface you prefer after testing demos. Performance differences are measurable but unlikely to significantly impact your bottom line.</p>
      </AnalystNotes>
    </div>
  </section>

